+# Unity 2D Prototype Client Studio Proof Checklist
+
+## Client Goal
+
+Turn the existing Unity 2D prototype title screen into a small portfolio proof slice with more intentional player-facing feedback while preserving the platformer gameplay sample.
+
+## Scope Lock
+
+- Keep the original platformer, actor damage, collection, door, switch, and projectile behavior.
+- Add title prompt polish only.
+- Preserve the existing `TitleMenu` scene entry flow and audio transition.
+- Do not add new art, paid assets, scene rewiring, or broad manager refactors.
+
+## Formal Art Direction
+
+- Keep the existing pixel-platformer / learning-prototype visual identity.
+- Treat the title prompt as a player-facing UI moment, not a debug label.
+- Use TextMeshPro color motion rather than canvas placeholders or temporary OnGUI.
+- Keep motion subtle enough that the title remains readable.
+
+## Architecture Boundary
+
+- `TitleMenu.cs` owns title-screen UI prompt motion and start input gating.
+- `GameManager.cs` remains global scene restart and escape behavior only.
+- `Platformer2DController.cs` remains player input translation.
+- `Actor.cs` remains health, damage feedback, and death response.
+- `AudioManager` scripts remain audio playback services.
+
+## QA Checklist
+
+| Check | Expected |
+|---|---|
+| Prompt pulse | Start prompt alpha pulses when reduced motion is disabled. |
+| Reduced motion | Prompt returns to base alpha when `ReducedMotion` is enabled. |
+| Start input | Keyboard input can start the game when no mouse button is pressed. |
+| Mouse guard | Left, right, and middle mouse buttons do not accidentally start the game. |
+| Start flow | Start text hides, title audio stops, confirmation audio plays, and the next scene loads. |
+| Architecture | Gameplay, actor, and manager scripts do not own title UI prompt animation. |
+
+## Acceptance Criteria
+
+- Player-facing title UI has intentional non-blocking feedback.
+- UI motion is separated from gameplay and scene management.
+- Reduced-motion behavior exists for the prompt effect.
+- Static smoke passes.
+- Runtime Unity play mode is required before final client acceptance.
+
+## Ruthless Playtester Note
+
+The title screen now feels less dead, but the project still needs a real HUD and a clearer first-level objective before it can feel like more than a learning sample.
